02:02.957 --> 02:05.525
Man over radio: <i>Forced evictions are
underway in what some are calling</i>

02:05.559 --> 02:08.560
<i>the radicalization</i>
<i>of Mayor Kane.</i>

02:08.595 --> 02:11.029
<i>Though residents of the</i>
<i>poverty-stricken Lennox Gardens</i>

02:11.062 --> 02:13.331
<i>are slated to occupy</i>
<i>the foreclosed homes</i>

02:13.366 --> 02:16.735
<i>of those being asked to leave</i>
<i>in middleclass neighborhoods,</i>

02:16.769 --> 02:19.070
<i>not all believe</i>
<i>they'll be able to return</i>

02:19.104 --> 02:22.373
<i>to the refurbished development</i>
<i>as promised by the mayor.</i>

02:23.158 --> 02:24.324
( Radio turns off )

02:45.045 --> 02:46.778
Hello, Emma.

02:46.813 --> 02:48.447
Is your father home?

02:49.549 --> 02:51.316
No.

02:51.350 --> 02:52.851
Your mother?

02:52.885 --> 02:55.120
( Ticking )

02:55.154 --> 02:57.856
( Sighs )

03:00.660 --> 03:02.594
( Ticking )

03:04.230 --> 03:06.598
<i>( Footsteps approaching )</i>

03:08.134 --> 03:10.402
Mrs. Kane,
nice to see you.

03:10.436 --> 03:12.371
Sorry for the disturbance.

03:12.405 --> 03:14.873
- Is there a problem?
- I hope not.

03:14.908 --> 03:16.909
Do you happen to know
where the mayor is?

03:16.943 --> 03:18.877
- He's not at City Hall?
- No.

03:18.912 --> 03:21.580
Did he come home last night?

03:21.615 --> 03:25.016
I ask only because I've been unable to
reach him by phone, text, or emails

03:25.051 --> 03:27.352
since he left the office
rather abruptly yesterday.

03:27.386 --> 03:28.621
What do you mean?

03:28.655 --> 03:31.656
From what I'm told, he was last seen
cursing about a pothole on Chestnut

03:31.691 --> 03:35.127
before he asked his driver for the
keys and left without explanation.

03:37.630 --> 03:39.565
I thought it best
to ask you first

03:39.599 --> 03:41.133
before taking other measures

03:41.167 --> 03:43.068
in the event that
the mayor's unavailability

03:43.102 --> 03:45.737
was personal in nature.

03:45.771 --> 03:47.772
Mrs. Kane?

03:49.341 --> 03:51.309
There's no cause for concern,

03:51.343 --> 03:53.011
if that's what you're asking.

03:54.045 --> 03:56.248
Certainly.
I don't mean to pry, but...

03:56.282 --> 03:58.817
Tom needs his space sometimes.

03:58.852 --> 04:02.721
Why don't you try checking his
true home in Lake Point Tower?

04:04.424 --> 04:06.759
Sorry to disillusion you.

04:10.931 --> 04:13.833
Maybe he's run away from home.

04:19.839 --> 04:21.606
Officer: <i>Fellas, I need</i>
<i>this block clear.</i>

04:21.641 --> 04:23.108
All right?
We'll be here all day.

04:23.142 --> 04:25.243
Come on, folks, let's make this

04:25.277 --> 04:28.246
as easy as we can
for everybody concerned.

04:33.753 --> 04:37.589
Sure wasn't a garden,
but it was home.

04:37.623 --> 04:39.625
- Come on, come on.
- <i>( Banging )</i>

04:39.659 --> 04:41.193
Officer: By order
of the city of Chicago,

04:41.227 --> 04:42.728
you need to vacate
the premises.

04:42.762 --> 04:44.496
You knew this was coming.

04:44.530 --> 04:46.098
Either you come out
or we're going in.

04:46.132 --> 04:48.167
Man: <i>I ain't going nowhere.
Fuck you all!</i>

04:55.309 --> 04:56.509
Reporter:
A sheriff was injured

04:56.543 --> 04:58.444
in the eviction
of an unruly tenant.

04:58.479 --> 05:01.147
Is this going to be a longer day
than you and your team anticipated?

05:01.182 --> 05:02.916
Man: There's no question
it's gonna be a long day...

05:02.950 --> 05:04.784
Looking more and more
like a death march.

05:04.818 --> 05:07.286
- It just needs context.
- Well, we're 10 minutes away.

05:07.321 --> 05:09.755
- Without him I don't have any.
- Postpone the presser.

05:09.789 --> 05:11.657
With any luck
he'll be here by midday.

05:11.691 --> 05:13.826
Man: But I think if we
really stay together...

05:13.860 --> 05:17.296
Oh, shit. This is about a
minute from going sideways.

05:17.330 --> 05:20.466
And where the hell is he
that he can't be reached?

05:20.500 --> 05:22.868
Sick? Hung over?

05:22.903 --> 05:24.904
- Mistress in another country?
- I'll tell you where he isn't...

05:24.938 --> 05:26.572
his home or his
private apartment.

05:26.606 --> 05:28.091
Private apartment?

05:28.092 --> 05:29.575
Doorman says he hasn't
been there in weeks.

05:29.609 --> 05:31.344
( Sighs )

05:31.378 --> 05:34.581
Okay, first thing we need to do is
make sure the sheriffs stand down,

05:34.615 --> 05:38.150
<i>not overreact to any understandable</i>
<i>displays of resistance.</i>

05:38.185 --> 05:39.819
You think they'll take
that order from an aide?

05:39.853 --> 05:43.189
Our office to theirs.
That's all they need to know.

05:43.224 --> 05:45.625
Not gonna be able to hold
off the dogs for long.

05:45.659 --> 05:48.228
- So, what do we do?
- Manage.

05:48.262 --> 05:50.063
And keep trying to find him.

05:50.097 --> 05:51.831
I'll see if there's
anything in his office

05:51.865 --> 05:54.100
that sheds light
on his whereabouts.

05:55.936 --> 05:58.037
Reporter ♪2: Should Lennox
Gardens families benefit

05:58.072 --> 06:00.706
<i>from the plight of homeowners</i>
<i>who've been foreclosed upon?</i>

06:00.741 --> 06:03.042
<i>Some in this neighborhood</i>
<i>feel if anyone needs</i>

06:03.076 --> 06:05.878
<i>subsidized help</i>
<i>from the city, they do</i>

06:05.913 --> 06:08.949
<i>to keep from losing homes they've
paid mortgages on for years.</i>

06:08.983 --> 06:11.952
<i>And with at least as many as eight dozen</i>
<i>Lennox Gardens families</i>

06:11.986 --> 06:14.054
<i>moving into</i>
<i>this neighborhood alone,</i>

06:14.088 --> 06:17.024
<i>some are suggesting</i>
<i>they may not be welcome.</i>

06:36.811 --> 06:40.914
- ( Touch tones beeping )
- <i>( Rings )</i>

06:40.949 --> 06:43.951
Woman: <i>Alternalive Treatment Centre.
How may I assist you?</i>

06:43.985 --> 06:45.452
Yes, good morning.

06:45.487 --> 06:46.954
I wonder if you could tell me

06:46.988 --> 06:49.423
if Thomas Kane
checked in overnight.

06:49.457 --> 06:50.925
This is his wife calling.

06:50.959 --> 06:52.426
I apologize, ma'am.

06:52.461 --> 06:54.261
I'm not at liberty to give out
patient information.

06:54.296 --> 06:55.663
<i>I understand.</i>

06:56.932 --> 06:59.100
My husband
is an elected official

06:59.134 --> 07:01.002
of a major American city.

07:01.036 --> 07:05.306
I'd hate to turn this into a
political headache for your clinic.

07:06.775 --> 07:09.410
<i>Yes, Mr. Kane is here.</i>

07:09.445 --> 07:10.912
Thank you.

07:10.946 --> 07:12.847
Doctor:
<i>Tell me what's happening.</i>

07:12.881 --> 07:15.583
<i>( Ezra's voice echoing ) You
can't because you don't know.</i>

07:15.617 --> 07:17.085
Voices.

07:17.119 --> 07:19.621
- A voice...
- Ezra: <i>I'm not just a voice.</i>

07:19.655 --> 07:22.090
I hear in my head.

07:22.124 --> 07:25.527
- Saying what?
- Nothing of import.

07:25.561 --> 07:27.362
Any visual hallucinations?

07:27.397 --> 07:29.365
Ezra: <i>You can't because you...</i>
<i>what's the difference?</i>

07:29.399 --> 07:32.701
- Stop asking questions.
- Excuse me?

07:32.736 --> 07:36.105
You have been paid,
arrangements made.

07:36.139 --> 07:37.840
Doctor: <i>Mr. Kane, this is</i>
<i>a delicate process.</i>

07:37.874 --> 07:39.341
Undoubtedly you've run
a background check.

07:39.375 --> 07:40.876
You know who I am,
where I'm from,

07:40.910 --> 07:42.711
and that I don't have
any time to waste.

07:42.746 --> 07:46.250
So may we start
the fucking treatment, please?!

07:46.284 --> 07:47.751
Based on your intake,

07:47.786 --> 07:49.219
we're looking
at a three-step regimen

07:49.254 --> 07:51.322
involving stem cells
for regeneration,

07:51.356 --> 07:53.323
a bark-based infusion
for sedation,

07:53.358 --> 07:56.293
and electroconvulsive
therapy for activation.

07:56.327 --> 07:58.028
Ezra: <i>Nonsense.</i>
<i>It's all nonsense.</i>

07:58.062 --> 08:02.332
We'll start with biofeedback
to test your visual cognition.

08:02.367 --> 08:04.001
<i>Please have a seat.</i>

08:04.035 --> 08:06.503
Ezra: <i>None of it will work.
It's a waste of time.</i>

08:06.537 --> 08:09.039
<i>You can't stop this now.</i>
<i>You can't stop me,</i>

08:09.073 --> 08:12.709
<i>because it's already done,</i>
<i>the damage.</i>

08:12.743 --> 08:14.978
<i>You hurt me, you're only</i>
<i>hurting yourself.</i>

08:15.012 --> 08:16.914
<i>( Projector clicks )</i>

08:16.948 --> 08:18.582
Tell me what you see.

08:18.617 --> 08:20.952
Ezra:
<i>Caitlin Mills,</i>

08:20.986 --> 08:25.523
<i>raped in the '93 riots</i>
<i>brought on in Lennox Gardens.</i>

08:25.558 --> 08:26.991
<i>Remember?</i>
<i>Sound familiar?</i>

08:27.025 --> 08:30.094
- Nothing.
- Ezra: <i>Caitlin Mills.</i>

08:30.128 --> 08:32.361
- <i>Caitlin Mills.</i>
- Mr. Kane, in order for this to work,

08:32.397 --> 08:34.097
I need your full cooperation.

08:34.131 --> 08:36.900
Ezra:
<i>Caitlin Mills.</i>

08:36.934 --> 08:40.169
<i>Charles Kingston,</i>
<i>burned to death.</i>

08:40.205 --> 08:43.941
- <i>Charles Kingston.</i>
- Are you in any pain?

08:43.976 --> 08:48.446
Ezra: <i>Tracy LaSalle,</i>
<i>Hector Alvarez, Joseph Clark.</i>

08:48.480 --> 08:51.315
<i>Shot, stabbed...</i>
<i>what does it matter?</i>

08:51.350 --> 08:54.318
<i>It's not as though you're</i>
<i>personally responsible.</i>

08:54.353 --> 08:56.021
Doctor: <i>Mr. Kane.</i>

08:56.022 --> 08:57.688
Ezra: <i>But you are
responsible, aren't you?</i>

08:57.722 --> 09:01.625
<i>Shot, stabbed...</i>
<i>what does it matter?</i>

09:01.660 --> 09:03.662
A girl.

09:03.663 --> 09:05.663
<i>It's not as though you're
personally responsible.</i>

09:05.697 --> 09:07.699
<i>But you are responsible...</i>

09:10.836 --> 09:12.837
<i>( Distant sirens wailing )</i>

09:30.055 --> 09:32.590
( Sighs )

09:51.478 --> 09:54.480
( Sighs )

10:19.138 --> 10:19.905
<i>( Knocks )</i>

10:19.906 --> 10:21.672
Reporter: The mayor's plan
for the peaceful relocation...

10:21.407 --> 10:22.040
Excuse me, sir.

10:22.074 --> 10:23.542
There's a guy here
from "The Sentinel"

10:23.576 --> 10:25.310
who's aggressively
requesting to see you.

10:25.345 --> 10:28.113
Yes, but I am not interested in an
interview about your wife and Zajac

10:28.147 --> 10:29.748
like every other
reporter in town.

10:29.783 --> 10:32.751
Hey, man, what part of "wait here"
don't you understand?

10:32.786 --> 10:36.922
Mr. Miller, since when
do editors do interviews?

10:36.957 --> 10:38.491
Since I'm just as interested

10:38.525 --> 10:41.227
in holding Tom Kane accountable
for his actions as you are.

10:41.261 --> 10:43.462
Reporter: <i>Some residents are crying
foul over what they believe</i>

10:43.497 --> 10:45.998
<i>is an attack</i>
<i>on civil liberties.</i>

10:47.267 --> 10:49.168
- ( Phones ringing )
- Zajac Campaign.

10:51.037 --> 10:53.238
His only comment is no comment.

10:53.272 --> 10:55.974
( Phones ringing )

10:58.177 --> 11:01.179
I'm sorry, but he's not speaking
with the press at this time.

11:01.214 --> 11:04.383
<i>( Phones ringing )</i>

11:04.417 --> 11:06.085
So how do we fix what's broken?

11:06.119 --> 11:08.621
Empty promises?
Cookie-cutter solutions?

11:08.655 --> 11:10.489
Things that haven't
worked before won't again.

11:11.524 --> 11:14.460
And business as usual will
give us the usual business.

11:14.494 --> 11:16.161
We need to listen
to each other,

11:16.195 --> 11:19.798
<i>respond to our real concerns</i>
<i>with real solutions.</i>

11:19.832 --> 11:22.334
<i>This isn't about</i>
<i>left, right, rich, poor.</i>

11:22.368 --> 11:24.770
It's about fixing
what's wrong for all of us.

11:25.304 --> 11:26.305
Right, buddy?

11:28.808 --> 11:30.308
Reporter:
<i>With foreclosures growing</i>

11:30.343 --> 11:32.411
<i>at an alarming rate</i>
<i>in the Chicago area,</i>

11:32.445 --> 11:35.681
the mayor has joined forces
with a number of local banks

11:35.715 --> 11:38.350
to offer up homes
with defaulted loans

11:38.384 --> 11:40.919
as temporary rentals
to displace

11:40.953 --> 11:42.621
<i>Lennox Gardens' residents.</i>

11:42.655 --> 11:44.356
<i>Many of these homes,</i>
<i>however, remain occupied...</i>

11:44.390 --> 11:46.625
Hey, if you don't mind,
I'm gonna take lunch.

11:46.659 --> 11:49.061
- <i>( Phones continue ringing )</i>
- Sure.

11:50.430 --> 11:51.430
Hey.

11:52.799 --> 11:54.299
Thanks for sticking this out.

11:54.333 --> 11:56.335
Reporter: <i>...Have rallied around</i>
<i>one longtime neighbor</i>

11:56.369 --> 11:59.038
<i>who stands to lose his home</i>
<i>by the end of the day.</i>

11:59.072 --> 12:00.706
<i>Tell us your feelings, sir.</i>

12:00.740 --> 12:03.242
Homeowner: Good people are being
forced out of their homes

12:03.276 --> 12:06.412
by those who created the problems
to begin with... the banks.

12:06.446 --> 12:10.282
Actually, I'm gonna go home.

12:10.316 --> 12:13.585
Homeowner: <i>They're the ones who
broke their promises to us.</i>

12:13.619 --> 12:16.521
<i>Now me and my family,</i>
<i>we're homeless.</i>

12:16.555 --> 12:18.690
<i>The mayor's looking out</i>
<i>for those other people.</i>

12:18.724 --> 12:21.059
<i>Who's looking out for us?</i>

12:23.262 --> 12:25.830
<i>( Birds chirping )</i>

12:25.865 --> 12:29.134
Tina, we have to focus
on the campaign.

12:29.168 --> 12:31.070
<i>This is ridiculous.</i>

12:31.104 --> 12:33.906
You're being incredibly
petty right now.

12:33.940 --> 12:35.474
<i>Uh, we'll talk</i>
<i>about this later.</i>

12:35.509 --> 12:37.977
Kitty's here.

12:38.011 --> 12:40.946
- Morning.
- First time in four campaigns

12:40.981 --> 12:43.949
Cook County is oh-so-possibly
ours for the taking.

12:43.983 --> 12:48.086
My longtime staffers don't know
what to do with themselves.

12:49.189 --> 12:51.190
Tina's upset
because I wanna move

12:51.224 --> 12:53.726
my headquarters to Chicago

12:53.760 --> 12:56.361
with you at the helm.

12:56.396 --> 12:57.896
Oh.

12:58.898 --> 13:01.266
Are you game?

13:02.051 --> 13:03.669
Of course.

13:04.203 --> 13:05.537
Good.

13:05.572 --> 13:07.039
Just don't get used to it.

13:07.073 --> 13:09.975
Soon enough, I'll have you
with me in Springfield.

13:12.746 --> 13:14.480
This mass eviction thing
is turning ugly.

13:14.514 --> 13:16.082
Do you want me
to head over there?

13:16.116 --> 13:18.017
Chuck, why did no one,
including myself,

13:18.052 --> 13:20.086
uncover the fact that
right beneath our eyes

13:20.120 --> 13:21.988
a few months back
there was an internal plot

13:22.022 --> 13:23.957
to run Zajac
for mayor of Chicago

13:23.991 --> 13:25.759
instead of
governor of Illinois?

13:25.793 --> 13:28.628
A plot that might have come to pass
had he not been caught on camera

13:28.662 --> 13:30.963
screwing the wife
of the man who hatched it,

13:30.998 --> 13:32.532
i.e. Alderman Ross.

13:32.566 --> 13:36.035
I mean, how come Kane can crack
that story, but we can't?

13:36.069 --> 13:40.339
Um, there have been six arrests
made at Lennox Gardens.

13:41.341 --> 13:42.808
Well, what are you waiting for?

13:42.842 --> 13:44.576
Get out there.

13:48.547 --> 13:51.749
Ezra: <i>This is just a fantasy.
I'm still here.</i>

13:51.783 --> 13:53.584
<i>Did you think you could escape?</i>
<i>There's no remedy.</i>

13:53.618 --> 13:55.352
- <i>There's only resistance!</i>
- <i>( Classical music playing )</i>

13:55.386 --> 13:57.621
<i>You can't tune me out, Tom.</i>
<i>A wish!</i>

13:57.655 --> 13:59.790
- <i>I'm not going anywhere.</i>
- ( Volume increases )

13:59.825 --> 14:02.994
<i>I'm the only thing that makes sense!
A wish.</i>

14:03.028 --> 14:04.929
<i>I'm the only one</i>
<i>who knows the truth.</i>

14:04.963 --> 14:06.497
- ( Tuning stations )
- <i>A distraction.</i>

14:06.532 --> 14:09.701
<i>There's no remedy.</i>
<i>There's only resistance.</i>

14:09.735 --> 14:12.671
Reporter: <i>Here in the windy city
where indeed a storm is brewing</i>

14:12.705 --> 14:15.908
<i>at the crossroads of public housing
and the subprime mortgage crisis.</i>

14:15.942 --> 14:18.210
<i>( Static buzzing )</i>

14:18.245 --> 14:20.880
<i>( Classical music playing )</i>

14:20.914 --> 14:22.948
Ezra: <i>And the only thing</i>
<i>that's real, Tom,</i>

14:22.983 --> 14:25.317
<i>is what I'm telling you.</i>

14:25.351 --> 14:28.019
<i>( Indistinct whispering )</i>

14:28.054 --> 14:29.855
- <i>( Distant sirens wailing )</i>
- <i>( Door opens )</i>

14:29.856 --> 14:31.289
Your lunch, sir.

14:32.024 --> 14:34.125
"God forbid we should
ever be 20 years

14:34.160 --> 14:35.894
without such a rebellion."

14:38.431 --> 14:39.430
( Laughs )

14:39.431 --> 14:41.933
Thomas Jefferson.

14:41.968 --> 14:43.368
You have some
reading to do, son,

14:43.402 --> 14:45.338
if you really wanna make
a go in this business.

14:45.372 --> 14:47.407
You know when Lennox Gardens
last blew up?

14:49.243 --> 14:52.145
1993.
You do the math.

14:53.147 --> 14:55.381
- 19 years.
- One shy of 20.

14:55.416 --> 14:58.084
What might Jefferson
himself recommend

14:58.118 --> 14:59.886
for a course of action today?

15:00.170 --> 15:01.670
Rebellion?

15:01.705 --> 15:04.039
If you say so.

15:04.074 --> 15:08.010
You are a man with
influence in the community

15:08.044 --> 15:09.677
<i>with foot soldiers at the ready</i>

15:09.712 --> 15:12.914
<i>who surely know</i>
<i>how to disturb the peace.</i>

15:12.948 --> 15:14.716
You mean light shit up?

15:14.751 --> 15:16.719
"And the rockets' red glare,

15:16.753 --> 15:19.221
the bombs bursting in air"...

15:19.255 --> 15:20.722
I assume that means more to you

15:20.757 --> 15:22.791
than drunken sing-alongs
at a Sox game.

15:22.825 --> 15:25.393
Sir, I was just hoping to have

15:25.428 --> 15:28.063
a more legitimate role
in things.

15:28.097 --> 15:31.499
As Kenya Taylor's replacement,
for example?

15:32.501 --> 15:34.636
<i>Ward boss of the 21st?</i>

15:38.141 --> 15:40.242
Is something
happening in Chicago?

15:40.276 --> 15:42.477
- Ezra: <i>It's burning to the ground.</i>
- I'm afraid I don't know.

15:42.512 --> 15:45.447
- What's that?
- Ezra: <i>Poison. Don't take it.</i>

15:45.482 --> 15:47.349
It's just for contrast,
Mr. Kane.

15:47.383 --> 15:49.017
Gives us a better MRI scan.

15:49.051 --> 15:51.587
Ezra:
<i>Why would you want that?</i>

15:51.621 --> 15:55.291
<i>They might see then</i>
<i>what you really are,</i>

15:55.325 --> 15:57.092
<i>everything that</i>
<i>you've ever done.</i>

15:57.126 --> 16:00.861
<i>That wouldn't be</i>
<i>a good thing, Tom...</i>

16:03.331 --> 16:05.866
<i>Because you are a bad man.</i>

16:06.401 --> 16:08.569
<i>You can't change it, Tom.</i>

16:08.604 --> 16:11.606
<i>( Whispering continues</i>
<i>indistinctly )</i>

16:14.042 --> 16:15.510
<i>( Ezra's laugh echoing )</i>

16:15.544 --> 16:18.579
( Machine knocking, humming )

16:18.614 --> 16:21.482
Ezra: <i>This is going to hurt you</i>
<i>more than it hurts me.</i>

16:21.517 --> 16:23.185
<i>( Sirens wailing )</i>

16:23.186 --> 16:24.853
Letting things play out
might only make them worse.

16:24.887 --> 16:26.921
I'll show you
affirmative action...

16:26.956 --> 16:29.357
a goddamn wrecking ball
on that dump.

16:29.391 --> 16:30.792
After all I've given you...

16:30.826 --> 16:35.263
your career, this office,
my own daughter!

16:35.298 --> 16:38.033
Half my time is spent cleaning
up the mess you left behind!

16:38.067 --> 16:39.768
Fuck him!

16:42.539 --> 16:45.541
- ( Gasping )
- <i>( Ezra whispering indistinctly )</i>

16:46.790 --> 16:49.041
<i>( Ezra whispering Was there something
you wanted to do with him?</i>

16:50.290 --> 16:51.941
<i>You remember, don't you.</i>

16:53.082 --> 16:56.351
You need to stay calm, sir.
Try not to get agitated.

16:56.885 --> 16:59.388
- Ezra: <i>You're a monster.</i>
- ( Breathing deeply )

17:04.359 --> 17:05.861
( Clears throat )

17:14.369 --> 17:16.002
Where are you going?

17:18.941 --> 17:21.141
I've recovered, sweetheart.

17:24.412 --> 17:27.046
I see no reason why
you can't do the same.

17:39.326 --> 17:41.328
City Hall, please.

17:45.734 --> 17:47.702
( Engine starts )

17:52.575 --> 17:54.909
( Siren wailing )

17:56.779 --> 17:59.814
Listen up, listen up!

17:59.848 --> 18:01.549
This is private
property, people.

18:01.583 --> 18:03.050
If you wanna protest the banks,

18:03.085 --> 18:06.654
I suggest you take it to
their door, not this one.

18:06.688 --> 18:09.857
Otherwise, you run the risk of
getting arrested for trespassing.

18:09.891 --> 18:12.525
- Hey, officer, maybe I can help.
- ( Crowd laughs, murmurs )

18:12.560 --> 18:14.994
- How are you doing, folks?
- ( People groaning )

18:15.029 --> 18:18.297
I know many of you have heard
a lot about me lately...

18:18.332 --> 18:21.000
( Crowd laughing, jeering )

18:21.034 --> 18:23.403
Ben: <i>I'm sure you take me as just
another bullshit politician.</i>

18:23.437 --> 18:25.473
Woman: <i>Yeah, exactly.</i>

18:25.474 --> 18:27.508
Hey, asshole, stop
using us for publicity.

18:27.542 --> 18:30.477
- Man: <i>That's right, man.</i>
- What publicity?

18:30.512 --> 18:32.813
Huh? You had the news here
this morning, right?

18:32.847 --> 18:34.515
For 10 minutes?

18:34.549 --> 18:37.150
But they're gone now and so is any
awareness of you or your neighbors

18:37.185 --> 18:39.819
who are getting evicted from their homes
they've been making payments on for years.

18:39.853 --> 18:42.155
- Hey, come on. Come on.
- Me? I've got a big spotlight on me.

18:42.189 --> 18:43.456
Use it.

18:46.027 --> 18:49.929
All right, everyone link
arms, make a chain.

18:49.964 --> 18:52.332
<i>Let's show the banks</i>
<i>what a fight looks like.</i>

19:01.142 --> 19:04.478
Officer: <i>You have 24 hours</i>
<i>to clear the property...</i>

19:04.512 --> 19:06.680
every last one of you.

19:06.715 --> 19:08.516
Reporter: <i>Police officers</i>
<i>on the scene are now saying</i>

19:08.550 --> 19:12.987
that the enforcement of mandatory
evacuations at Lennox Gardens

19:13.021 --> 19:15.055
have become increasingly
violent in the past hour...

19:15.090 --> 19:17.892
Moretti's getting slammed.
So is the city hall main line.

19:17.926 --> 19:20.527
Reporter: <i>...The mayor's efforts to
remove them from their homes...</i>

19:20.562 --> 19:22.830
You all right?

19:22.864 --> 19:24.866
No, I'm not.

19:27.235 --> 19:28.669
Ian:
<i>Wait, what are you doing?</i>

19:28.704 --> 19:31.472
- Where are you going?
- Someone needs to be there.

19:31.506 --> 19:34.708
You can't leave,
not when you're the...

19:35.977 --> 19:38.846
I mean, we're undermanned here.

19:38.880 --> 19:41.682
Reporter: <i>The previous owners were</i>
<i>evicted to make room for them.</i>

19:41.716 --> 19:44.351
<i>Thus far, no comment</i>
<i>from the mayor's office,</i>

19:44.386 --> 19:46.620
<i>but in what is her first</i>
<i>public appearance</i>

19:46.655 --> 19:48.556
since the shooting
that nearly took her life,

19:48.590 --> 19:50.924
- Chicago's first lady Meredith Kane...
- I thought she was on bed rest.

19:50.958 --> 19:52.859
<i>Arrived at City Hall</i>
<i>moments ago.</i>

19:52.894 --> 19:54.861
<i>Appearing fit and buoyant,</i>

19:54.896 --> 19:56.797
<i>she had this to say</i>
<i>to reporters.</i>

19:56.832 --> 19:58.633
Mrs. Kane,
how are you feeling?

19:59.367 --> 20:01.202
- Getting better.
- <i>Have you fully recovered?</i>

20:01.736 --> 20:03.237
Not quite,
but we're working on it.

20:03.272 --> 20:04.739
What brings you here today?

20:04.773 --> 20:06.708
Well, we just have
a lot of work.

20:06.742 --> 20:08.877
Mrs. Kane, do you have anything
to say to the people of Chicago?

20:09.411 --> 20:12.647
Just that I'm so grateful

20:12.682 --> 20:14.950
for their encouragement
and support.

20:14.984 --> 20:20.389
And it's wonderful
to be back among you,

20:20.423 --> 20:23.625
and it's wonderful
to be, again,

20:23.659 --> 20:25.493
in the service
of this great city

20:25.528 --> 20:27.963
and wonderful to be alive.

20:27.997 --> 20:29.998
Thank you so much.
Excuse me.

20:30.032 --> 20:31.499
- My husband's expecting me.
- <i>( Applause )</i>

20:31.534 --> 20:33.601
Man: <i>Welcome back! Welcome back!</i>

20:42.509 --> 20:43.977
Mr. Todd.

20:44.311 --> 20:45.278
You must be Mona.

20:45.313 --> 20:47.447
Yes. How may
I help you, Mrs. Kane?

20:47.482 --> 20:49.850
Close the door, please.

20:49.884 --> 20:52.352
<i>( Door closes )</i>

20:55.322 --> 20:57.390
Given the circumstances,
it seemed necessary

20:57.424 --> 20:59.959
to have all hands on deck.

20:59.993 --> 21:01.460
Ron, the press...

21:01.494 --> 21:03.862
let them know the mayor's
hunkered down on the fifth floor

21:03.896 --> 21:05.864
working to preempt any further
escalations of events.

21:05.898 --> 21:07.466
We'll need a cover story
if this situation spirals.

21:07.467 --> 21:08.833
Right.

21:08.868 --> 21:12.937
I'm sorry, but what exactly
are the circumstances?

21:12.972 --> 21:14.272
Where is the mayor?

21:14.306 --> 21:15.740
You'll be apprised soon enough.

21:16.775 --> 21:18.610
Until then, I believe
you have a job to perform

21:18.645 --> 21:20.312
either way.

21:22.015 --> 21:24.617
My understanding is that
you've been a prime mover

21:24.651 --> 21:26.920
behind things
at Lennox Gardens,

21:26.954 --> 21:29.355
which suggests you bear
a certain burden

21:29.390 --> 21:31.391
to see this powder keg
contained.

21:31.426 --> 21:33.661
( Chimes )

21:36.764 --> 21:38.865
Council leadership
is calling for

21:38.899 --> 21:40.834
an emergency meeting
in the chambers.

21:40.868 --> 21:43.803
How do you propose
we handle that, Mrs. Kane?

21:47.808 --> 21:50.276
Here in the conference room,

21:50.311 --> 21:52.779
away from the prying eyes
of the press.

21:55.032 --> 21:56.316
That'll be all for now.

22:03.690 --> 22:06.258
"Bear a certain burden"?

22:06.293 --> 22:09.128
Fuck you.

22:09.162 --> 22:12.331
Did she just take
the reins like that?

22:12.366 --> 22:14.166
I think she did.

22:15.435 --> 22:16.902
All right, y'all.

22:16.936 --> 22:20.839
Stick to the chain stores,
no mom-and-pops, all right?

22:20.874 --> 22:22.341
And we ain't Christmas
shopping neither, yo.

22:22.375 --> 22:25.077
<i>Hit one, move to the next.</i>

22:25.111 --> 22:28.246
All smash, no grab.
Keep it theatrical.

22:28.281 --> 22:29.748
( Mouths word )

22:29.782 --> 22:31.849
The game bigger than that
Blu-ray you trying to grab.

22:32.384 --> 22:34.886
Now come on, man.
Let's go.

22:41.628 --> 22:44.463
You still here?
What's wrong, Holmes?

22:44.497 --> 22:46.365
- You forgot your slugger or something?
- ( Glass shatters )

22:46.399 --> 22:48.901
I'm not...
I'm not doing it, man.

22:48.936 --> 22:51.571
( Laughing )
You're not doing it.

22:51.605 --> 22:53.272
I'm sorry.

22:53.306 --> 22:55.841
- Did you mistake that for an option?
- <i>( Alarms blaring )</i>

22:55.876 --> 22:59.445
Look, man, I'll sling for
you and I'll fight for you.

22:59.479 --> 23:03.215
But this?
For what?

23:03.250 --> 23:05.318
You know your problem?

23:05.352 --> 23:07.587
You're too weak to lead,

23:07.621 --> 23:10.456
but you can't follow either.

23:10.491 --> 23:12.025
Tssh.

23:12.059 --> 23:14.727
You're wasting my time.
I gotta get back to work.

23:14.762 --> 23:16.763
Now get out.

23:21.902 --> 23:24.538
- Don't slam my door neith...
- ( Door slams )

23:24.572 --> 23:26.406
( Sighs )

23:26.441 --> 23:29.810
Ezra: <i>You're not in charge.
You're not in control.</i>

23:29.844 --> 23:32.045
- ( Cell phone chimes )
- Doctor: <i>The stem cells</i>

23:32.079 --> 23:35.081
<i>are injected directly</i>
<i>into the spinal cord.</i>

23:35.116 --> 23:36.750
Ezra:
<i>She can't be trusted.</i>

23:36.784 --> 23:39.652
Doctor: This allows for
immediate travel to the brain.

23:39.687 --> 23:41.988
Ezra: <i>Neither can he.
Neither can this.</i>

23:42.022 --> 23:44.023
Doctor: <i>Mr. Kane, it's time</i>
<i>to put away the phone.</i>

23:44.057 --> 23:46.292
Ezra: <i>Leave. Go home.
They need you there.</i>

23:46.326 --> 23:49.195
To be distracted
in any way, to move...

23:49.230 --> 23:51.097
you could cause serious damage.

23:51.132 --> 23:53.199
- It's my wife.
- <i>( Ezra's laugh echoing )</i>

23:53.234 --> 23:55.702
Please, just give me a moment.

23:55.736 --> 23:58.372
- Ezra: <i>Before the damage is done.</i>
- ( Beeps )

23:58.406 --> 24:00.373
Ezra:
<i>You're a monster.</i>

24:00.408 --> 24:03.777
<i>You're insane.</i>
<i>( Laughing )</i>

24:03.811 --> 24:07.014
With the first injection,
the pain may be sharp,

24:07.048 --> 24:08.916
possibly inducing white flashes

24:08.950 --> 24:10.417
<i>or a momentary loss</i>
<i>of eyesight.</i>

24:10.452 --> 24:12.586
Ezra:
<i>Despicable.</i>

24:12.620 --> 24:15.756
<i>It's too late.</i>
<i>You did it already.</i>

24:15.790 --> 24:17.424
<i>How can you ever pay for it...</i>

24:17.459 --> 24:19.293
<i>all the damage you've done?</i>

24:19.327 --> 24:21.562
<i>There's not a punishment</i>
<i>enough for you,</i>

24:21.596 --> 24:23.297
<i>not even this, Tom.</i>

24:23.331 --> 24:24.898
<i>Not even this.</i>

24:24.933 --> 24:26.900
<i>You're despicable.</i>

24:26.935 --> 24:30.204
<i>You're a louse</i>
<i>of a human being.</i>

24:30.238 --> 24:32.507
<i>You should kill yourself</i>

24:32.541 --> 24:35.843
- <i>because you're disgust...</i>
- <i>( High-frequency whining )</i>

24:39.348 --> 24:42.983
- <i>( Reporters clamoring )</i>
- Reporter: <i>Six are dead.</i>

24:43.018 --> 24:46.053
<i>Six are dead.</i>

24:46.088 --> 24:48.155
<i>Six are dead.</i>

24:48.190 --> 24:51.191
Mr. Mayor, Mr. Mayor,
Mr. Mayor, six are dead,

24:51.226 --> 24:54.395
arson's spreading, reportedly the
rape of a 12-year-old girl...

24:54.429 --> 24:57.065
<i>could this be the day that haunts
your legacy for years to come?</i>

24:57.099 --> 24:58.566
No, I... I don't
believe it will.

24:58.601 --> 25:01.836
<i>( Reporters clamoring )</i>

25:01.871 --> 25:03.705
Reporter ♪2: <i>Is your
inaction a direct result</i>

25:03.740 --> 25:05.774
<i>of citywide budget cuts?</i>

25:05.808 --> 25:06.942
Is this a public shaming

25:06.976 --> 25:08.410
of the Chicago Housing Authority?

25:08.445 --> 25:09.846
Deliberation is not inaction.

25:09.880 --> 25:13.650
- It's simply...
- <i>( Reporters shouting )</i>

25:13.684 --> 25:16.886
Are rumors true, Mr. Mayor,
that the former mayor Rutledge

25:16.920 --> 25:18.721
is involved in decisions
being made behind the scenes?

25:18.755 --> 25:20.889
No! Who the hell
told you that?

25:20.924 --> 25:23.859
( Silence )

25:23.893 --> 25:26.328
<i>( Ezra's laugh echoing )</i>

25:31.600 --> 25:33.635
Meredith:
I'm so grateful

25:33.669 --> 25:35.770
for their encouragement
and support.

25:35.804 --> 25:40.742
<i>It's wonderful to be back</i>
<i>among you, and...</i>

25:40.776 --> 25:42.477
Wow, I mean,

25:42.512 --> 25:47.450
she is absolutely genius at distraction.

25:47.484 --> 25:49.451
Can someone please tell me
where Tom Kane is

25:49.486 --> 25:51.186
before this whole city
goes up in flames?

25:51.221 --> 25:52.655
- His office?
- Why?

25:52.689 --> 25:54.356
Because Moretti said so?

25:54.391 --> 25:57.460
<i>I mean, Churchill could go</i>
<i>on radio in World War II</i>

25:57.494 --> 25:58.962
from his bunker
in a blitzkrieg,

25:58.996 --> 26:00.564
but Kane is too hunkered down

26:00.598 --> 26:03.367
to appear before the cameras?

26:03.401 --> 26:05.502
( Ringing )

26:08.707 --> 26:10.707
Kitty:
<i>Hey, can we talk?</i>

26:10.742 --> 26:12.910
That would be a start.

26:12.944 --> 26:16.013
Look, I'm not good
at this sort of thing, okay?

26:16.047 --> 26:17.615
What sort of thing is that?

26:17.649 --> 26:19.450
Please don't make this
any harder than it already is.

26:21.820 --> 26:23.321
I'm not.

26:23.355 --> 26:27.926
I'm just trying to understand
what we're doing here,

26:27.960 --> 26:29.694
what this is between us.

26:29.729 --> 26:31.964
I don't know,

26:31.998 --> 26:34.399
but the reality is
you're a journalist.

26:35.734 --> 26:38.069
I won't take that as an insult.

26:38.103 --> 26:41.272
And I'm... whatever,
an operative.

26:41.306 --> 26:43.374
I'm sensing some
pretty blurry boundaries.

26:43.408 --> 26:44.976
I'm willing to stay in my Lane

26:45.010 --> 26:46.711
if you're willing
to do the same.

26:46.746 --> 26:48.380
Okay.

26:48.414 --> 26:50.449
- Why?
- <i>I'm not sure.</i>

26:50.483 --> 26:53.285
( Laughs )

26:53.320 --> 26:55.354
I like you.

26:55.389 --> 26:58.857
I'm gonna be back in Chicago
for a while on the campaign.

26:58.892 --> 27:01.360
<i>You need more than that?</i>

27:01.394 --> 27:03.728
I'll take more than
a phone call.

27:05.498 --> 27:07.065
Hello, everyone.

27:07.099 --> 27:09.667
Thank you for agreeing
to join us upstairs.

27:10.702 --> 27:12.203
First and foremost,

27:12.237 --> 27:14.271
the mayor is fine
and in control.

27:14.306 --> 27:15.906
<i>I've just been</i>
<i>in touch with him.</i>

27:15.940 --> 27:19.343
<i>But what I'm about to tell you</i>
<i>is not to leave this room</i>

27:19.377 --> 27:21.845
and, for reasons of security,
is not what the public

27:21.880 --> 27:24.114
<i>has been or will be told.</i>

27:24.148 --> 27:26.283
So please, respect
the sensitivity.

27:26.317 --> 27:29.587
<i>Late last night, before this
morning's troubles began,</i>

27:29.621 --> 27:33.024
the mayor was summoned
to Washington by the FBI

27:33.058 --> 27:34.692
regarding matters
linked to the attempt

27:34.726 --> 27:37.729
<i>made on his life and mine.</i>

27:37.763 --> 27:39.764
The exact nature
of these matters

27:39.798 --> 27:42.500
even I cannot know
from my husband,

27:42.535 --> 27:45.703
but they appear to require
his urgent involvement.

27:45.738 --> 27:48.306
In DC now, as we speak?

27:48.341 --> 27:53.011
Meredith: <i>Yes, for time-sensitive
reasons as of late last night.</i>

27:53.045 --> 27:55.947
<i>I should add that given</i>
<i>the standard hostile relations</i>

27:55.982 --> 27:58.984
<i>between the FBI and</i>
<i>the State's Attorney's office,</i>

27:59.018 --> 28:02.921
even Mr. Doyle will not be
privy to the mayor's absence.

28:02.956 --> 28:05.257
- And he comes back when?
- As soon as he's able to.

28:05.291 --> 28:08.693
In the meantime, he is in constant
contact with Superintendent Royczyk,

28:08.728 --> 28:10.696
Chief Malley,
and Governor Cullen.

28:10.730 --> 28:13.765
<i>Anything he would do,</i>
<i>he's doing from there.</i>

28:13.799 --> 28:15.867
Except be here.

28:15.901 --> 28:17.669
Meredith:
<i>Alderman Ross,</i>

28:17.703 --> 28:19.270
I would hope there's enough
water under the bridge

28:19.305 --> 28:22.340
to wash away
the usual recriminations.

28:22.374 --> 28:25.310
The mayor's expecting
everyone's cooperation

28:25.344 --> 28:26.845
until he returns.

28:28.214 --> 28:30.582
Did you two know about this?

28:30.616 --> 28:32.651
As of early this morning.

28:32.686 --> 28:34.486
Hmm.

28:35.271 --> 28:38.891
Will the mayor be available
to join us by speakerphone?

28:38.926 --> 28:41.861
Not for the moment.

28:41.896 --> 28:44.064
Now then, to the
situation at hand.

28:49.103 --> 28:50.570
<i>( Protesters chanting )</i>
<i>...We won't go!</i>

28:50.604 --> 28:53.840
<i>Hell no, we won't go!</i>
<i>Hell no, we won't go!</i>

28:53.874 --> 28:57.143
Hell no, we won't go!
Hell no, we won't go!

28:57.178 --> 28:59.412
How long are all of you
planning on staying here?

28:59.447 --> 29:01.548
Until the banks
give us an extension.

29:01.582 --> 29:03.917
And is it true that
State Treasurer Zajac

29:03.952 --> 29:06.987
- organized this protest?
- No, it's not.

29:07.021 --> 29:10.157
Mr. Zajac, is this an attempt to get
back in your wife's good graces?

29:10.191 --> 29:12.659
How do you plan to recover
from the scandal?

29:12.694 --> 29:14.795
I'm not the person
you need to be directing

29:14.829 --> 29:16.496
your questions at
about recovery.

29:16.531 --> 29:17.998
This man's about
to lose his home.

29:18.033 --> 29:20.434
And so is this woman and so is
that gentleman right there.

29:20.469 --> 29:23.071
( Cheering )

29:23.105 --> 29:24.706
Maybe if the press
was more interested

29:24.740 --> 29:26.808
in what's going on
in the real world

29:26.842 --> 29:28.843
instead of what's happening
in people's bedrooms,

29:28.878 --> 29:30.345
we wouldn't be in this mess.

29:30.379 --> 29:32.381
I'm just doing my job, okay?

29:32.415 --> 29:34.449
- Mr. Zajac, could you tell us...
- Get that shit out of my face!

29:34.484 --> 29:38.119
- You need to back off.
- Cool it. Just relax.

29:38.154 --> 29:40.621
- I said get that out of my face!
- Yo, man, what the fuck?

29:40.656 --> 29:41.989
Hey, hey.
Walk away.

29:42.023 --> 29:43.257
- Hey, back up.
- Whoa.

29:43.291 --> 29:44.424
Walk away.
Just walk away.

29:44.459 --> 29:46.760
You walk away,
you fuckin' douchebag.

29:46.794 --> 29:48.595
( All shouting )

29:48.629 --> 29:51.664
Eh! Eh! You break it up!
Break it up!

29:51.699 --> 29:54.133
Reporter: A surge of
vandalism is being reported

29:54.168 --> 29:56.436
in the areas surrounding
Lennox Gardens.

29:56.470 --> 29:59.972
Over a dozen businesses suffered
major property damage in...

30:00.006 --> 30:01.607
This whole thing's
gonna get out of control.

30:01.641 --> 30:03.943
He needs to say
something to the public.

30:03.977 --> 30:05.912
I'd settle for
his just being around.

30:05.946 --> 30:07.413
Reporter:
<i>...Prompting some to call</i>

30:07.447 --> 30:10.450
<i>for citywide increase</i>
<i>in police presence.</i>

30:10.484 --> 30:13.086
Bark of the iboga plant...

30:13.120 --> 30:15.087
medicinal tea... we
discussed... hallucinogenic.

30:15.122 --> 30:16.789
Ezra:
<i>Won't work. Poison.</i>

30:16.823 --> 30:19.726
<i>Mind... don't take it...</i>
<i>lose.</i>

30:19.760 --> 30:21.994
The tea...
you have to drink it.

30:22.029 --> 30:24.130
Ezra: <i>You don't even know</i>
<i>what's real any more.</i>

30:24.164 --> 30:25.665
- Hallucinogenic?
- Ezra: <i>You are.</i>

30:25.699 --> 30:28.700
With the brain
in a relaxed state,

30:28.735 --> 30:30.235
the stem cells have
a better chance

30:30.270 --> 30:31.971
at targeting
the diseased tissue.

30:32.005 --> 30:35.007
Ezra:
<i>This whole thing... fiction.</i>

30:35.041 --> 30:36.508
<i>( Laughter echoing )</i>

30:36.543 --> 30:38.443
What did you say?

30:38.478 --> 30:41.713
Studies have shown that
concentration on targeted areas

30:41.747 --> 30:45.049
<i>can play a supportive role</i>
<i>in healing treatments.</i>

30:45.083 --> 30:48.018
Ezra: <i>Face it,</i>
<i>nothing can fix you.</i>

30:48.053 --> 30:51.721
<i>Nothing can fix what you've
broken or who you've broken.</i>

30:51.756 --> 30:54.090
<i>( Laughter echoing )</i>

30:54.125 --> 30:56.593
Woman: <i>Might be nice if
you remembered my name.</i>

30:56.627 --> 30:58.795
What do you want?

31:00.164 --> 31:02.699
Woman: <i>Don't worry.
He doesn't know.</i>

31:02.734 --> 31:05.402
But I am done raising him alone

31:05.437 --> 31:07.238
with shit to show
for it on your part.

31:07.272 --> 31:09.340
I'm supposed to believe you?

31:09.374 --> 31:11.643
Now that you've waited
till I'm in office to tell me?

31:11.677 --> 31:13.779
<i>Come here again,</i>

31:13.813 --> 31:17.516
I will burn you
to a fucking crisp.

31:17.550 --> 31:19.651
Your son be damned.

31:41.574 --> 31:44.041
Tom:
<i>Get out!</i>

31:44.076 --> 31:46.577
I told the governor
you'll be calling him

31:46.612 --> 31:48.946
requesting the National Guard

31:48.981 --> 31:51.315
before this mess
blows up any further.

31:51.349 --> 31:52.983
Get out!

31:53.017 --> 31:54.418
- Tom!
- <i>( Door slams )</i>

31:54.452 --> 31:56.053
Either your father
truly retires

31:56.087 --> 31:59.123
or, so help me God,
I will take you down with me.

32:00.525 --> 32:04.361
<i>( Glockenspiel music playing )</i>

32:05.830 --> 32:08.565
- Who loves you?
- You do.

32:08.600 --> 32:09.967
Good answer.

32:13.639 --> 32:15.506
( Music continues )

32:19.812 --> 32:21.813
<i>( Distant sirens wailing )</i>

32:28.587 --> 32:32.022
Emma:
So, that's the grand tour.

32:33.291 --> 32:35.793
Now pay for the ticket, right?

32:35.827 --> 32:37.828
Stop.

32:42.033 --> 32:44.235
I couldn't get to any.

32:44.269 --> 32:47.205
<i>I can't even get into my place.</i>

32:47.240 --> 32:49.942
It's just all fucked up
over there now.

32:53.379 --> 32:56.114
Well, where are you
even staying, then?

33:03.990 --> 33:06.224
I don't even know.

33:11.631 --> 33:13.933
Well, um...

33:15.468 --> 33:17.403
- Is there any other way...
- ( Scoffs )

33:17.437 --> 33:19.271
Don't you have to take tests?

33:19.305 --> 33:22.341
Yeah, I do,
but it's not a problem.

33:22.375 --> 33:25.811
( Scoffs )
Maybe I should just go.

33:27.280 --> 33:29.948
No, no, no.
Don't, don't.

33:31.084 --> 33:33.085
We shouldn't...

33:55.077 --> 33:56.744
Meredith:
<i>Emma?</i>

33:58.581 --> 34:01.416
Oh... yeah?

34:03.419 --> 34:05.020
Good night.

34:05.054 --> 34:06.655
Good night.

34:15.998 --> 34:18.667
( Laughing )

34:21.337 --> 34:24.306
You mind if I ask you a...

34:24.341 --> 34:26.574
Potentially sensitive question?

34:26.609 --> 34:29.678
( Laughs )

34:29.712 --> 34:32.648
Do you ask any other kind?

34:34.918 --> 34:37.420
Thank you.

34:37.454 --> 34:42.793
Were you aware of the plot
to replace Kane with Zajac?

34:45.464 --> 34:46.931
Where'd you hear that?

34:46.965 --> 34:49.067
Meaning yes?

34:49.101 --> 34:51.737
Meaning

34:51.771 --> 34:53.906
who cares?

34:55.208 --> 34:57.409
Y-you know,
that's the second time

34:57.444 --> 35:01.146
you've shot me down when the
subject has turned to Zajac.

35:02.649 --> 35:05.784
All right, it's late.
I gotta go.

35:08.488 --> 35:10.922
No.
It's not safe.

35:11.458 --> 35:13.458
Don't go.

35:32.379 --> 35:36.149
Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa.
Hey, hey, hey, hey.

35:36.183 --> 35:38.518
I... I don't have
anywhere to go.

35:38.552 --> 35:40.920
Do you?

35:40.955 --> 35:43.156
Let's not rush.

35:45.393 --> 35:48.328
<i>( Kitty gasping )</i>

35:49.112 --> 35:50.464
Don't look at me like that.

35:50.498 --> 35:52.032
- Shut up.
- What?

35:52.067 --> 35:53.567
Look at me.

35:55.937 --> 35:57.638
You're fuckin' beautiful.

36:03.612 --> 36:06.614
- Shut up, Sam.
- Fuck you.

36:17.293 --> 36:20.094
Reporter: Vandalism, property
destruction, and a spate of violence

36:20.129 --> 36:22.630
has resulted in a growing
number of arrests tonight.

36:22.665 --> 36:24.699
Police are working
overtime to combat

36:24.733 --> 36:26.968
what appears to be
a groundswell of lawlessness

36:27.003 --> 36:29.404
apparently sparked
by today's mandatory...

36:29.439 --> 36:31.607
<i>( Sirens wailing )</i>

36:31.608 --> 36:33.775
Got the kids to sleep
despite all the sirens.

36:33.810 --> 36:35.844
Reporter: <i>Others have taken</i>
<i>to the streets to fight them</i>

36:35.878 --> 36:38.246
<i>or express their own rage</i>
<i>against the system,</i>

36:38.280 --> 36:39.747
<i>which raises the question...</i>

36:39.782 --> 36:42.983
- It'll settle down.
- I hope so.

36:43.018 --> 36:45.552
<i>To physical fights</i>
<i>to whole families of looters,</i>

36:45.586 --> 36:49.923
the city is on edge, even as neighbor
seems to be turning on neighbor.

36:49.958 --> 36:51.992
<i>( Distant sirens wailing )</i>

36:52.027 --> 36:54.128
<i>( Cell phone ringing )</i>

36:58.566 --> 37:00.633
Who's Jackie?

37:00.668 --> 37:03.203
She's a reporter at the paper.

37:03.237 --> 37:05.472
Jackies aren't
journalists, Sam.

37:05.506 --> 37:08.008
- They're strippers and waitresses.
- <i>( Ringing continues )</i>

37:09.911 --> 37:11.578
Says Kitty.

37:11.612 --> 37:14.381
( Both laugh )

37:14.416 --> 37:17.317
Hey.
No, I'm up.

37:19.020 --> 37:20.921
Where?

37:23.792 --> 37:26.594
All right, I'll come in.

37:26.629 --> 37:28.496
What happened?

37:30.566 --> 37:34.101
CPD shot an unarmed kid

37:34.136 --> 37:36.604
packing an iPod.

37:40.476 --> 37:43.211
Promise me you'll
come back tomorrow.

37:46.815 --> 37:50.251
- I can't promise you that.
- Shut up.

37:58.160 --> 37:59.194
<i>( Sirens blaring )</i>

37:59.195 --> 38:00.628
Reporter: Widespread
looting has continued...

38:00.662 --> 38:02.464
School's canceled.

38:02.498 --> 38:04.766
You need to stay home
with the kids.

38:08.171 --> 38:10.606
- Maybe you should stay, too.
- I can't.

38:11.390 --> 38:13.075
This is gonna get a lot worse.

38:14.811 --> 38:16.579
Reporter: Most schools
and many businesses

38:16.613 --> 38:18.781
have shuttered their doors
as a precaution.

38:18.815 --> 38:22.084
Police are asking that those who
can stay home today, please do so.

38:22.118 --> 38:24.520
Reporter ♪2: <i>In the overnight
shooting that has ratcheted</i>

38:24.554 --> 38:28.191
<i>yesterday's events, acts of arson
have spread throughout the city.</i>

38:28.225 --> 38:29.992
<i>People have taken</i>
<i>to the streets,</i>

38:30.026 --> 38:35.164
<i>and a disturbing repeat</i>
<i>of the '93 riots loom large.</i>

38:36.400 --> 38:39.201
Chicago Police have yet
to release a statement

38:39.235 --> 38:41.237
<i>about the shooting,</i>
<i>nor has the mayor.</i>

38:41.271 --> 38:44.039
<i>And, as some have said here,</i>
<i>the longer they wait,</i>

38:44.074 --> 38:45.908
<i>the more likely</i>
<i>there may be another...</i>

38:45.942 --> 38:48.410
Superintendent Royczyk is here.

38:48.445 --> 38:50.712
Great.
Send him in.

38:50.747 --> 38:52.214
<i>( TV turns off )</i>

38:52.248 --> 38:53.749
But what are you gonna say?

38:55.518 --> 38:58.620
I don't imagine you question
my husband in this fashion.

39:07.764 --> 39:10.265
Jim, so nice to see you.

39:11.050 --> 39:11.767
Meredith.

39:11.801 --> 39:13.335
He's here to discuss
last night's incident...

39:13.369 --> 39:16.038
Meredith: The superintendent and his
wife are longtime family friends.

39:16.072 --> 39:18.140
We've quite a history
together, don't we?

39:18.174 --> 39:20.209
And I think we'd prefer
to speak privately,

39:20.243 --> 39:22.177
if you don't mind.

39:24.214 --> 39:25.714
We'll be right outside.

39:34.357 --> 39:38.160
How long do we have to stand by
and agree to this charade?

39:38.194 --> 39:40.228
He could have been
abducted for all we know.

39:40.263 --> 39:42.397
That's the point...
we don't know anything.

39:42.431 --> 39:44.633
Clearly, Mrs. Kane does.

39:44.667 --> 39:46.835
I don't buy this FBI story.

39:46.869 --> 39:49.871
- Do you?
- I've got no reason not to.

39:49.905 --> 39:51.873
She was spot-on
about this much...

39:51.907 --> 39:53.508
the State's Attorney
and the Bureau

39:53.542 --> 39:57.746
do not share intel at all.

39:57.780 --> 40:00.515
Meredith: <i>I assume word leaked to you
about Tom being summoned to DC.</i>

40:00.549 --> 40:02.384
Royczyk:
<i>Yes.</i>

40:02.418 --> 40:05.220
I also heard that the mayor
and I have been in touch,

40:05.254 --> 40:07.522
which isn't true.

40:07.557 --> 40:09.024
( Sighs )

40:09.058 --> 40:10.892
An obvious miscommunication.

40:13.329 --> 40:17.032
Jim, a clean conscience

40:17.066 --> 40:19.000
can wait in situations
like this,

40:19.035 --> 40:21.002
clean streets cannot.

40:21.037 --> 40:22.671
What do you need
to make that happen?

40:25.308 --> 40:28.543
Direct word from Tom
endorsing the use

40:28.578 --> 40:30.912
of armored vehicles
and tactical squads

40:30.947 --> 40:34.483
to contain the hot spots
where unrest is spreading.

40:34.517 --> 40:37.019
Hmm, of course.

40:37.053 --> 40:41.156
Unless it was
deemed wiser to look

40:41.191 --> 40:44.927
to the National Guard
for the same.

40:46.596 --> 40:49.264
So, Cullen's in charge
with Kane gone?

40:49.298 --> 40:50.932
Here's what needs to happen...

40:50.967 --> 40:53.635
a public statement
to the press by you

40:53.669 --> 40:56.705
that given the unrest and the
heightened security concerns,

40:56.740 --> 40:59.374
with the attempted
assassination case still open,

40:59.409 --> 41:02.945
it's been decided that mayor Kane
should stay out of the public eye

41:02.980 --> 41:05.781
until the dust settles,
et cetera, et cetera.

41:05.815 --> 41:08.017
How does that make
for clean streets?

41:08.051 --> 41:10.386
One step at a time.

41:10.420 --> 41:12.121
And after
last night's shooting,

41:12.155 --> 41:14.990
I imagine that your next step

41:15.025 --> 41:19.028
is doing what it takes
to keep your job, no?

41:23.399 --> 41:25.801
Due to heightened
security concerns,

41:25.835 --> 41:27.537
it has been deemed necessary

41:27.571 --> 41:30.006
that the mayor remain
in a secure location.

41:30.040 --> 41:31.774
Reporter:
<i>Is he still in the city?</i>

41:31.809 --> 41:34.644
I would ask that you direct your
questions to the mayor's office.

41:34.678 --> 41:36.845
I'm required elsewhere.
Thank you very much.

41:36.880 --> 41:38.881
- ( Reporters clamoring )
- Superintendent, where is he?

41:38.916 --> 41:41.017
<i>Superintendent, where is he?</i>

41:42.419 --> 41:45.421
<i>( Sirens wailing,</i>
<i>police radio chatter )</i>

41:47.591 --> 41:49.391
<i>( Knocking )</i>

41:49.426 --> 41:52.895
- Homeowner: This is bullshit.
- Everyone relax. Don't resist.

41:52.929 --> 41:55.031
This will get straightened out
when you see a judge.

41:55.065 --> 41:56.833
Homeowner: <i>I'm just trying to</i>
<i>take care of my family.</i>

41:56.867 --> 41:59.369
- <i>This could happen to any of you!</i>
- ( All shouting )

42:01.905 --> 42:04.807
After hours of seemingly
unending violence,

42:04.842 --> 42:08.144
<i>the toll of injury</i>
<i>and destruction is growing.</i>

42:08.178 --> 42:10.147
<i>With fires burning</i>
<i>and rampant looting</i>

42:10.181 --> 42:14.284
<i>in a number of areas,</i>
<i>the city is under siege.</i>

42:14.818 --> 42:18.088
Did you think for a moment that
you had transcendent purpose

42:18.122 --> 42:21.691
or that somehow you were
worthy of being remembered?

42:21.725 --> 42:24.227
<i>A sanitation clerk</i>
<i>who had the audacity</i>

42:24.261 --> 42:26.830
<i>to fuck the mayor's daughter.</i>

42:26.864 --> 42:30.166
How dare you think
that you should ever

42:30.201 --> 42:32.602
have been put in the position

42:32.636 --> 42:34.938
to decide the fate of others?

42:34.972 --> 42:39.743
<i>That is a mantle to be worn</i>
<i>only by the great,</i>

42:39.777 --> 42:43.781
not by a man who wormed
his way into City Hall

42:43.815 --> 42:45.482
for a period of time.

42:45.517 --> 42:48.685
You're a chapter, a portrait,

42:48.720 --> 42:52.889
a handful of legislation,
a thousand lies,

42:52.924 --> 42:56.092
and yet

42:56.127 --> 42:59.162
you cling to power,

42:59.196 --> 43:02.899
falsely believing
you actually possess it.

43:02.934 --> 43:06.302
But your superiority
of force, of will,

43:06.337 --> 43:10.107
your control...
it's all an illusion

43:10.141 --> 43:14.511
because you're
still dying, Tom!

43:15.646 --> 43:17.514
And that terrifies you,
doesn't it?

43:17.548 --> 43:20.150
That you'll end up
just like me...

43:20.184 --> 43:25.389
dust no one misses.

43:29.226 --> 43:33.129
<i>( Ezra's laughter echoing )</i>

43:33.163 --> 43:35.364
How dangerous is this?

43:35.399 --> 43:38.300
Doctor: <i>ECT has a stigma</i>
<i>it does not deserve.</i>

43:38.335 --> 43:39.802
<i>Not only is this</i>
<i>the final phase</i>

43:39.836 --> 43:41.671
<i>of treatment,</i>
<i>but the most crucial.</i>

43:41.705 --> 43:44.039
It stimulates regeneration
of the diseased tissue.

43:44.074 --> 43:45.875
Can it kill him?

43:45.909 --> 43:48.210
Doctor:
<i>Kill you? No.</i>

43:48.244 --> 43:50.479
<i>That's not gonna happen.</i>

43:50.514 --> 43:52.081
Ezra:
<i>Once wasn't enough, Tom?</i>

43:52.115 --> 43:54.316
You can't kill a dead man...

43:56.820 --> 43:58.654
But you can
take responsibility.

43:58.688 --> 44:00.789
<i>( Ezra's laugh echoing )</i>

44:00.824 --> 44:03.825
Fucking die already.

44:04.827 --> 44:08.396
( Humming )

44:08.430 --> 44:09.964
<i>( Electricity crackles )</i>

44:12.334 --> 44:15.169
( Printer screeching )

44:20.475 --> 44:22.142
Who says I didn't
prevent Attica

44:22.177 --> 44:24.812
on a metropolitan scale
by not sending in the troops?

44:24.846 --> 44:27.448
Let my legacy burn
on your watch?

44:27.482 --> 44:29.383
I'll think of something.

44:30.452 --> 44:34.855
He had a stroke...
my father.

44:35.189 --> 44:37.324
The fat lady sings.

44:39.794 --> 44:42.196
Don't move.

44:44.600 --> 44:47.602
Turning off the water
to riotous neighborhoods

44:47.637 --> 44:50.272
is a page from
Stalin's handbook.

44:50.806 --> 44:52.274
A stroke.

44:52.559 --> 44:54.343
The stain will be permanent.

44:54.378 --> 44:56.211
- There's no way around that.
- <i>( High-frequency whining )</i>

45:02.852 --> 45:07.622
Oversight will be required
for his recovery...

45:09.190 --> 45:11.290
Or lack thereof.

45:11.324 --> 45:13.059
( Echoes ) Gentlemen.

45:14.962 --> 45:16.128
( Beeping )

45:18.332 --> 45:20.199
( Electricity crackling )

45:20.233 --> 45:21.867
The riots may be over...

45:21.902 --> 45:24.003
You piece of shit.

45:24.038 --> 45:25.671
<i>But not the fallout.</i>

45:25.706 --> 45:27.006
What do you want, money?

45:27.041 --> 45:28.741
No, that's a vile accusation!

45:29.843 --> 45:31.344
"What do you want,
<i>Barbara?"</i>

45:31.378 --> 45:33.814
- ( Electricity crackling )
- Oh, there's my girl.

45:41.022 --> 45:44.290
- I don't understand.
- That makes two of us.

45:44.325 --> 45:45.825
Where'd you get the urine?

45:48.162 --> 45:50.029
Where did I get it?

45:50.064 --> 45:52.132
Don't bullshit a bullshitter.

45:52.166 --> 45:54.334
<i>My guy at the lab says</i>
<i>you could date-rape Godzilla</i>

45:54.368 --> 45:56.102
<i>with that cocktail</i>
<i>in your system.</i>

45:56.136 --> 45:58.504
Bulbocapnine...

45:58.538 --> 46:02.441
some kind of inhibitor drug that
suppresses reflexes and muscle activity.

46:02.476 --> 46:06.012
<i>Used to induce a severe stupor.</i>

46:08.348 --> 46:10.349
<i>There something</i>
<i>you wanna share?</i>

46:15.356 --> 46:17.023
Okay, I'll tell you what...

46:17.057 --> 46:18.691
the police are stretched
pretty thin today.

46:18.726 --> 46:20.426
I'm on call to help out.

46:20.461 --> 46:22.495
Maybe there's a way
that I don't violate you

46:22.530 --> 46:24.931
between now
and the next appointment.

46:34.574 --> 46:36.442
<i>( Sirens wailing )</i>

46:36.476 --> 46:39.911
<i>( Fire engine horns honking )</i>

46:46.919 --> 46:48.920
<i>( Helicopter blades whirring )</i>

46:52.057 --> 46:53.591
Mrs. Kane, any word?

46:55.894 --> 46:57.595
Not yet.

46:59.899 --> 47:01.800
Do you need me to do
anything for you?

47:09.007 --> 47:10.674
Get me Governor Cullen.

47:20.585 --> 47:22.353
Reporter: With no signs
of abatement, city police

47:22.387 --> 47:24.422
and fire departments
are overwhelmed.

47:24.456 --> 47:27.058
Riot units, armed with
batons and tear gas,

47:27.092 --> 47:30.595
have been unable to quell what
appears to be a full-scale riot.

47:30.630 --> 47:33.665
Many Chicagoans are afraid to
step outside their front doors,

47:33.700 --> 47:35.500
<i>and those who do are likely...</i>

47:35.535 --> 47:37.302
Here we go again.

47:37.337 --> 47:39.204
( Phone rings )

47:39.238 --> 47:42.541
- Meredith?
- <i>Hello, Mac.</i>

47:42.575 --> 47:45.010
Things up there must be
worse than they look

47:45.044 --> 47:48.780
for you to be calling me or...
I don't know what to think.

47:48.815 --> 47:52.450
We've always had a mutual
respect, Mac, you and I.

47:52.485 --> 47:56.021
We have, you being cut from the
same cloth as your father.

47:58.925 --> 48:01.193
20 years ago, he urged Tom

48:01.228 --> 48:02.928
to ask Governor Dunham
for a deployment

48:02.963 --> 48:05.598
of the National Guard
to quell the riots.

48:06.132 --> 48:07.400
In hindsight it was

48:07.434 --> 48:10.370
- <i>Tom's first mistake as mayor.</i>
- But not his last.

48:10.904 --> 48:14.374
I would like to prevent the same
mistake from happening twice,

48:14.408 --> 48:18.011
<i>and only your office</i>
<i>has the power</i>

48:18.045 --> 48:20.313
<i>to reach both city and state.</i>

48:23.718 --> 48:25.719
I'd like to hear it from him.

48:25.753 --> 48:29.723
You will in due time.

48:29.758 --> 48:31.258
On my honor.

48:37.032 --> 48:40.134
Mac: <i>As the outgoing governor</i>
<i>of this great State,</i>

48:40.169 --> 48:43.872
<i>it is with pride and regret that
one of my last actions in office</i>

48:43.906 --> 48:45.974
will be a deployment
of the National Guard

48:46.008 --> 48:47.876
to quell the strife
in Chicago...

48:48.410 --> 48:51.245
regret that such a situation
ever came to this,

48:51.280 --> 48:56.451
<i>but pride that we the people of
Illinois would face it head on.</i>

48:56.485 --> 48:58.286
<i>I've been in touch</i>
<i>with the mayor's office there</i>

48:58.320 --> 49:00.488
and will remain so
until the unrest

49:00.523 --> 49:02.156
has fully subsided.

49:02.191 --> 49:03.758
She pulled the trigger on this?

49:03.793 --> 49:05.260
I don't think
you'll be disappointed

49:05.294 --> 49:06.796
by the mayor's
inevitable reaction.

49:06.831 --> 49:08.666
While State Senator Walsh
and I have had

49:08.700 --> 49:10.734
our disagreements in the past,

49:10.769 --> 49:13.838
her proposed bill denying
felons the right to vote

49:13.872 --> 49:16.908
<i>can't reach my desk</i>
<i>fast enough.</i>

49:16.942 --> 49:18.776
Did he just endorse
Walsh for governor?

49:18.811 --> 49:23.047
Those responsible for the crimes
of the past two days in Chicago

49:23.081 --> 49:27.418
will have no say in who
their future leaders are.

49:27.452 --> 49:29.086
Thank you.

49:31.590 --> 49:34.191
Reporter: As many as 4,000
national guardsmen have arrived...

49:34.226 --> 49:35.693
Wow.

49:35.727 --> 49:39.530
- Peace is restored.
- ( Ringing )

49:41.467 --> 49:43.534
Uh, give me a sec?

49:45.604 --> 49:47.238
Hey.

49:47.272 --> 49:49.807
Hey. Takeout's
getting cold.

49:49.841 --> 49:51.909
<i>Looks like I'm gonna be late</i>
<i>with all the troops in town.</i>

49:51.943 --> 49:54.445
What's up with Cullen
going public, but not Kane?

49:54.479 --> 49:56.213
<i>It's not strategic timing</i>
<i>on his part,</i>

49:56.248 --> 49:59.417
<i>it's just</i>
<i>a good old no-show.</i>

49:59.451 --> 50:02.119
<i>I mean, the question is why?</i>

50:03.955 --> 50:06.357
- Sam?
- <i>Yeah.</i>

50:08.727 --> 50:11.629
The papers on your table...

50:11.664 --> 50:12.664
Rosebud.

50:14.232 --> 50:15.366
Okay.

50:15.401 --> 50:17.468
<i>That's who leaked the
Bensenville document, right?</i>

50:19.663 --> 50:22.273
I'm pretty sure
the handwriting's Stone's.

50:30.549 --> 50:34.586
- Doctor: <i>Tell me what you see.</i>
- <i>( Projector clicks )</i>

50:34.620 --> 50:36.121
A beach.

50:40.227 --> 50:42.328
A bouquet of flowers.

50:44.265 --> 50:46.333
Ice cream.

50:46.367 --> 50:48.735
<i>( Projector clicks )</i>

50:52.574 --> 50:54.842
A desert.

51:01.082 --> 51:04.218
Emma:
<i>Grandpa? Grandpa.</i>

51:04.752 --> 51:07.555
Grandpa, did they...

51:08.339 --> 51:11.325
Did they do this to you?

51:11.360 --> 51:14.362
<i>Grandpa, did they?</i>

